Unfortunately, now this type is not fully correct.

The second version of the packages is always returns `root` node:

```js
{ type: 'root', children: [] }
```

https://github.com/Rich-Harris/svg-parser/blob/734f11b37397eafed09a4688a505972d9f5613b7/src/index.js#L231-L234
https://github.com/Rich-Harris/svg-parser/blob/master/test/samples/empty-svg/output.json

We can make this place better by always returning the `RootNode` node. Something like it:

```js
export type RootNode {
  type: 'root';
  children: TextNode | ElementNode;
}
```

